From: WaveCrux Pro capture pipeline
Subject: [PATCH] Add `aresetn` (active-low) to the FST dump

The Pro `Axi4FullDecoder` requires an `aresetn` binding (active-low
synchronous reset). Forencich's testbenches drive `rst` active-high.
We expose the inverted reset in the same testbench-side dump scope so
the FST carries the signal natively — no DUT modification, no decoder
change.

Apply with `patch -p1` from any verilog-axi `tb/<testbench>/` directory:

    patch -p1 < forencich_aresetn_dump.patch

Tested against `alexforencich/verilog-axi` commit
`516bd5dadc3365b7f9e225d2af8fe0b8d804fe53`.

---
 iverilog_dump.v | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/iverilog_dump.v b/iverilog_dump.v
--- a/iverilog_dump.v
+++ b/iverilog_dump.v
@@ -1,6 +1,8 @@
 module iverilog_dump();
+wire aresetn = !axi_ram.rst;
 initial begin
     $dumpfile("axi_ram.fst");
     $dumpvars(0, axi_ram);
+    $dumpvars(0, iverilog_dump.aresetn);
 end
 endmodule
